Another change that he made in printing was to antedate the letter by two months and more. Why he did this I cannot conjecture. Presumably, as with Epp. 333, 3 35, he wished the public to believe that the letter was written a con- siderable while before it actually was. The mouth-date of the ms. may be accepted in view of other letters to the Netherlands dated on the same day (Epp. 1471-3).
